      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HARA'S FRANKIE (8) produced a moderate run last time when fifth at this track over 600m behind Bad And Bertha (35.30) in a Grade 4/5. Placed at her previous run. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings three times from six starts. Ready to return to form. HIGHWAY PRINCESS (1) had been in sparkling form with a two start winning streak coming to an end last time finishing second (19.72) at Capalaba. Form at the trip excellent including five wins. Meets a moderate line up and should run well. CHEERS FOR BELLA (4) box seated before sticking on well to finish 1.3 lengths away in second (34.85) at this track in a Grade 4/5 over 600m. Recorded one of the quickest times on the card last start despite being beaten. Will give a great sight again. AKELA JUDO (6) is always a threat when he draws this box.",
